Prepare the apple filling. Cut apples into 1‚Ä≥ chunks, removing any cores and seeds, and add to a large bowl. Add remaining ingredients and toss well with a spoon or spatular until everything is coated. Set aside. Prepare the crisp topping by adding all ingredients to a bowl, except the oats. Use your hands to squeeze the ingredients together with the butter until you have a finer consistency and have broken down the butter. Add the oats in and work them into the topic with your hands. Pour the apple filling into a your bakeware, then crumble the crisp all over the top, spreading it out as evenly as you can. Bake for 45-55 minutes until it is bubbling and golden. Remove from oven and allow to cool for 10 minutes before serving.

text: Mac and Cheese from scratch #homemade #macandcheese #tradwife #maha #realfood Cheese Sauce 2 tbsp butter 3 tbsp einkorn flour 1 ¬Ω tsp ground mustard 2 cups whole milk 3 cups cheese, shredded Salt + pepper Elbow Pasta 4 cups einkorn flour, freshly milled, whole wheat, or all-purpose 4 pasture raised eggs Make pasta. Add flour to workspace in shape of a pyramid. Make a large hole for the eggs. Crack 4 eggs into hole, then whisk the eggs inside of the hole w a fork. Begin to whisk some flour from the sides into the eggs and continue to do this until you have whisked all of the flour into the eggs. Use your hands to bring all flour into the dough and knead until you have a softer dough. Dough will be firm, but may also be sticky, so its helpful to use a dough scraper. Let dough rest for 15 min. Once dough has rested, take dough scraper and cut dough into small pieces, roll into little balls bw your palms. Balls should be small. Place balls into your pasta attachment, allowing pasta to come through. Lay pasta onto dishcloth. Make your cheese sauce. Melt butter over medium heat in a medium-large pot or large saucepan. Use a whisk or a silicone spatula to whisk in the flour and ground mustard so that there aren‚Äôt any clumps. Over medium heat, slowly whisk in milk, stirring constantly to keep consistency thick and to press out clumps as they form. Do not add milk all at once. Continue whisking for several minutes until thick and bubbling. Turn heat down to low, then add in shredded cheese and allow it to melt while you stir. Season cheese sauce w salt and pepper. Cook the pasta in boiling water for 5 minutes until al dente. Strain water, pour pasta into pan w cheese sauce.

Homemade Snickers üç´ #snickers #realfood #homemade #recipe #tradwife Nougat 1 egg white 1/2 cup sugar 1/4 tsp 1 tbsp water 1/4 maple syrup Using a hand mixer, beat egg white until stiff peaks have formed. Next, cut the remaining nougat ingredients, stirring frequently until 250F. Slowly drizzle the thick syrup into the egg white, while mixing at medium-low until the mixture is thick, smooth and satiny. Pour this into a parchment lined baking dish and spread until even. Move to the fridge for a few hours to firm up. Caramel Nut Filling 1/3 cup sugar 6 tbsp butter 4 tbsp water 2 tbsp cream 1/2 cup almonds, chopped When nougat is firm, make the filling by cooking the sugar, butter and water until thick, then adding the cream in at the end and stirring until well combined and thick. Remove from heat and add the almonds. Pour this overtop the nougat and move to the fridge to firm up for 30-40 minutes. Chocolate 1 cup cacao butter 1/4 cup maple syrup 3/4 cup cacao powder 1 tsp vanilla Pinch of salt Melt the cacao butter, then remove from heat and stir in the remaining ingredinets. Make the snickers. Remove the parchment from the dish and cut into rectangles or small pieces. Carefully dunk each piece into the chocolate then place back onto parchment lined baking sheet. Place in the fridge to firm up - 10 minutes. Then, do a double dunk, and place the chocolates back onto the baking sheet and into the fridge. When firm, they‚Äôre done! These can be kept at room temperature, they won‚Äôt melt once they‚Äôre firm.

Homemade Reese‚Äôs #reeses #halloween #realfood #healthylife #tradwife Filling ‚Äî 1/2 cup nut butter or sunflower butter 2 tbsp butter 2 tbsp coconut sugar 1 tbsp coconut flour Warm the filling ingredients just enough to combine all ingredients well. Filling: 24 oz cream cheese 1 cup sour cream 1 cup pumpkin flesh 1/2 cup coconut sugar 3 tsp pumpkin pie spice 1 tsp vanilla 2 pinches sea salt 2 eggs In a stand mixer Beat cream cheese until fluffy, then add sour cream. Bake at 300F for 40 minutes, then turn heat off and open oven door half way to allow cheesecake to slowly cool down. Remove from oven after 1 hour and cool to room temperature, then transfer to fridge for several hours or overnight until cold. Caramel: 2 tbsp coconut sugar 1 tbsp water 2 tbsp butter Combine in ingredients in small saucepan and bring to simmer, stirring constantly until thickened. Don‚Äôt overheat. Topping: 2 cups cream 1 tbsp maple syrup 1/2 tsp vanilla 1 tsp cinnamon In a stand mixer, mix all ingredients until cream turns into whipped cream. Don‚Äôt overmix or it will turn to butter. Drizzle caramel over cheesecake, then top with fresh whip. Enjoy!

Zucchini muffins w/ fermented einkorn #homemade #islandlife #healthymom  Pre-Batter 3 cups whole wheat einkorn flour ¬º cup to¬†‚Öì cup sourdough discard  (active or inactive) 1¬º cup raw milk Final Batter 2 eggs ¬Ω cup coconut oil, melted 2-3 tbsp coconut sugar ¬Ω tsp unrefined salt 1 tsp baking soda ¬Ω tsp cinnamon 1 tsp vanilla 1 cup zucchini, grated finely 1 cup wild blueberries, frozen or fresh Step 1 Combine pre-batter ingredients in a medium-large bowl until well combined. Batter should be very thick, but not dry, so add small amount of additional milk if needed. Cover with cling wrap and let sit on the counter at room temperature to ferment overnight. Step 2 In the morning, batter should look risen and puffy. Preheat oven to 425F. Step 3 Add all final batter ingredients, except zucchini and blueberries, to pre-batter and stir until well combined. Add shredded zucchini and combine well. Lastly, fold in blueberries. Step 4 Grease a 12 x muffin pan with coconut oil or use unbleached parchment muffin cups liners. Use a ¬º cup measuring cup to scoop batter into each muffin cup. Fill to top. Step 5 Bake at 425F for 7 minutes, then turn temperature down to 375F for remaining 18 minutes. Muffins should be golden on top. Step 6 Remove from oven and let sit to cool for 10 minutes. Carefully remove each muffins and let cool on a rack or enjoy right away.

Peach Upside Down Cake üçëü•Æ #peaches #einkorn #cake #summerdessert #healthylifestyle #tradwife #homemaker STEP 1: Prepare Cake Pan 3 peaches, sliced Grease a cake pan well using butter. Recipe üëá #tradwife üíóFermented Sourdough Discard Raspberry Choc Chunk Muffinsüíó Pre-Batter Ingredients: 1 cup sourdough discard 1 3/4 cup einkorn berries, milled into flour or about 3.5 cups whole wheat einkorn flour 1/2 cup plain yogurt 1/4 cup coconut sugar 1/4 cup raw milk  2 eggs 1 tsp vanilla 1/2 cup butter, melted (1 stick) Combine all ingredients in a bowl. Batter should be pretty thick. Start by using less milk first and add more if need be. Then, cover with plastic wrap and let sit to ferment overnight on the counter. Final Batter Ingredients: 1/2 tsp salt  1 tsp baking soda 3-4 tbsp coconut sugar 1 1/2 cups frozen raspberries Choc chunks In the morning, add salt, baking soda, coconut sugar, choc chunks and frozen raspberries to the batter. Use a cookie scoop or measuring cup to put the batter into muffin pan. Bake at 425F for 7 minutes, then turn temp down to 375F and bake for 15 more minutes.

Caldo de Res is a Mexican beef soup with veggies and beef broth. It‚Äôs so delicious and provides lots of leftovers. It comes together very easily too. My husband loves this dish and I feel good about feeding it to my family too :) Enjoy the recipe! #tradwife #homemade #mexicanfood #caldoderes  Caldo de Rez Slow cut beef cuts and bones or bone in shank Unrefined salt to flavor Fresh ground pepper 1 onion, peeled and chopped 6-12 garlic cloves, peeled 1 cabbage, cut into large chunks  4-5 carrots, peeled and chopped 5 potatoes, peeled and chopped Several corn on cobs or bagged frozen corn Filtered Water Brown meat on all sides, salt and pepper generously, then add pieces and bones to a large stock pop of boiling water. Deglaze the pot with onions garlic, and broth from the stockpot, then add this into stockpot.  Season the water with salt and pepper to flavor the broth. Simmer for several hours until meat is falling off the bone, then add the. Carrots, cabbage and potato and cook for about 20 minutes. The corn can be added in towards the end. Plate each bowl with fresh cilantro or dried cilantro flowers and pickled radish and sauerkraut. Serve with warm tortillas.

Recipe üëá ‚Äî My einkorn source can be found at gretchy.com OREO Cookies 3/4 cup butter, room temp 1/4 cup coconut sugar 1 tsp vanilla 3/4 tsp unrefined salt 1 egg, room temp  1/2 cacao powder 2 cups all purpose einkorn flour Cream together butter + sugar, add in vanilla and salt. Add egg + mix until incorporated and fluffy. Slowly add cacao powder and einkorn flour, little by little. Squeeze dough together with parchment paper, then roll it out between two pieces of paper until 1/8‚Äù - 1/4‚Äù thick. Try to make a rectangle the size of baking sheet.  Transfer to baking sheet, remove top paper. Use cookie cutter to cut circles, then remove the trimmings. Use trimmings and repeat the process until none is left. Bake at 350F for 12-15 minutes. Remove from oven and let cool. Cookies will harden as they cool. Filling 2 sticks butter, room temp 1 tsp vanilla 3/4 cup maple sugar Possible flour addition Whip butter until soft and fluffy and white about 2 minutes. Add vanilla. Add maple sugar and whip 2 minutes. Frost cookies. Refrigerate if frosting gets too soft. #tradwife #homemade #oreos

Oreo Cookie Crust Chocolate Pie üíó recipe üëá ‚Äî My prenatal is linked profile w a discount code Oreo Cookie Pie Crust ‚Äî 3/4 cup butter, room temp 1/4 cup coconut sugar 1 tsp vanilla 3/4 tsp unrefined salt 1 egg, room temp  1/2 cacao powder 2 cups all purpose einkorn flour 1 stick or 1/2 cup butter, melted Cream together butter + sugar, add in vanilla and salt. Add egg + mix until incorporated. Slowly add cacao powder, then flour, little by little.  Squeeze dough together with parchment paper, then roll it out between two pieces of paper until 1/4‚Äù thick. Transfer to baking sheet, remove top paper, and bake at 350F for 15 minutes. Remove from oven and let cool. Break into pieces + use rolling pin to smash into sm. crumbs. Add melted butter and stir well. Line a pie dish w the Oreo crumbs + shape w measuring cup. Bake at 350F for 20 min, then cool. Chocolate ‚Äî  1 cup cacao 1 cup cacao butter 3 tbsp coconut sugar  Melt ingredients in small pot. Set melted chocolate aside, about 7-8oz, and reserve rest to make a chocolate bar for shaving later. Freeze bar until ready. Chocolate Filling ‚Äî 1 cup raw cream 4 eggs, room temp 1/2 cup coconut sugar 3/4 cup butter, room temp 1 tsp vanilla  Whipped Cream ‚Äî  1 cup raw cream 1-2 tbsp maple syrup Whip in stand mixer. 1. Whip the cream in stand mixer until stiff, then refrigerate for later. 2. Using a double broiler, whisk eggs and coconut sugar constantly for several min until it reaches 160F. Remove from heat and let cool for 10 minutes. 3. Using stand mixer, whip butter + vanilla until fluffy, 2 min.  4. Add homemade liquid chocolate to eggs and stir well. Add to stand mixer with butter and whip well. 5. Fold in cold whipped cream to chocolate mixture. 6. Layer pie crust w chocolate filling + fresh whipped cream.  7. Shave chocolate bar + garnish pie. Frigerate for several hours. serve chilled. #tradwife #haileybieber

Know your wheat üíó recipe üëá #wheat #einkorn #tradwife #homemadebagels  SOURDOUGH BAGELS 4.5 cup einkorn berries or 8-9 cup whole wheat einkorn flour 3 tsp unrefined sea salt 3 TBSP coconut sugar 3/4 cup active sourdough starter 1.5 cup warm water 1. Mix starter, water + sugar in lrg bowl, add flour and salt and mix until a shaggy dough is formed. Add a little water if needed. 2. Pour olive oil on top of the dough, then use a scraper to move dough to counter. 3. Knead dough w/ olive oil until its softer, then place back in bowl for 15 min. 4. Remove dough + knead for a few more min until softer. Do this step again if you have time. 5. Cover with plastic wrap or plate and let ferment all day. 6. When dough has risen significantly and is puffy, move to fridge in evening. 7. Next day, remove bowl from fridge. Cut dough into small pieces to form bagels. 8. Grab sides of each piece + gather underneath the ball of dough, then roll to form a ball. Make hole in center. 9. Place bagels on greased baking sheet. Cover. Let rise 1-3 hours until puffy. May take shorter or longer. 10. Preheat oven to 500F w baking sheet 11. Boil water + add 2 tsp baking soda to water. Cook each bagel for 30 seconds per side, then remove and set on drying rack. 12. Bake on preheated baking sheet for 5 min at 500F, then 400F for 15 min.

Birria for dinner üåÆ Recipe üëá #tradwife #birria #tacos #homemade Ingredients and Directions ‚Äî Meat: 1 4-5 lb beef chuck or shoulder 4 bay leaves Salt the meat and sear on all sides. Set aside while you make the Chile sauce. Chile Sauce: 1/2 onion 6 garlic 8 guajillo peppers, dried 8 California peppers, dried 3-4 cups water 1 tbsp oregano 1 tbsp thyme 1 tsp cumin 5 whole cloves 1 tbsp whole black peppercorns Several large pinches salt Cook all ingredients in water for about 10 minutes until the peppers are soft. Remove the tips. Add cooked ingredients into a blender with all dried herbs and salt. Reserve the water and add a bit into the blender until it blends well, but doesn‚Äôt need to be too much water. Add Chile sauce to the meat through a strainer and stir until all that‚Äôs left in the seed pulp. You may add more water to thin it out frequently while you stir. Add a bunch of water so that meat is almost covered in water. Bring to boil then let simmer for several hours 4-6 hours ideal until meat is easily shreddable. When meat is done, shred in the pot. Dip hot tortillas in the sauce first, then compile tacos with desired toppings. Eat immediately!

Beef breakfast sausage üêÑ #homemade #homemaker #sausage Recipe ‚Äî 2lbs 100% grass fed ground beef 2 tsp unrefined salt Crushed black pepper 1 tsp sage 1 tsp thyme 1 tsp garlic powder 1 tsp onion powder 1 tsp fennel 1/2 tsp nutmeg 1/4 tsp cayenne pepper 2 tbsp coconut sugar Combine spices in a small bowl and stir well. Then, massage spice mix into ground beef in a larger bowl until well mixed. Let the mixture sit for overnight if you have the time to let flavors integrate. Cook the sausages in a good amount of tallow or coconut oil until browned on all sides. These store well in a container in the fridge. You can also freeze on a baking sheet, then grab as you need them. They cook in a few minutes to warm up.

Nothing like a homemde pie. #homemade #homemaker LEMON MERINGUE PIE Crust 3 cups all-purpose einkorn flour (link for source in profile) 1 tbsp maple sugar 1 tsp unrefined salt 1 cup (two sticks) cold butter, cut into cubes 1-4 tbsp ice cold water Mix flour, sugar, salt in bowl. Add butter. Work w your hands until it holds together. Add water slowly. Work dough into ball on counter. Cut in half, then flatten into 2 discs wrapped in parchment. Move to freezer or fridge for 1hr. Let dough come to room temp for 10 min when ready to roll out. Roll dough out to lrg circle. Place into pie dish. Shape edges. Freeze crust for 1hr until v hard. Add pie weights and bake at 425F for 15 min. Remove pie weights, use fork to make holes, then bake for 5-10 min more until cooked and golden brown. Filling 5 egg yolks 1/2 cup maple sugar 1/2 cup all-purpose einkorn flour 1/4 tsp unrefined salt 1 1/4 cups water 3/4 cups lemon juice Zest of several lemons 4 tbsp butter, cubed Separate yolks and whites. In mixing bowl, whisk yolks. In small pot, combine maple sugar, flour, salt. Whisk in water, lemon juice, zest until smooth. On medium heat whisk often until thickened and starting to bubble ‚Äî 5 min. Turn off heat. Temper egg yolks by slowly pouring a little hot lemon custard into yolks, whisking constantly. Pour tempered eggs into lemon custard in pot. Whisk constantly over medium heat until thickened and bubbling, about 2 min. Remove from heat. Whisk in butter. Pour into baked pie crust. Meringue  5 egg whites 1/4 tsp cream of tartar 1/4 cup maple sugar Whisk egg whites and cream of tartar w/electric beaters. Slowly add maple sugar. Beat for a few min until velvety white and stiff peaks form. Final Bake Spread meringue on top of lemon custard. Bake at 350F for 20 min until meringue is golden brown. Let come to room temp / Chill before serving. #tradwife

text: I take taco night v seriously. #homemade #nixtamal #tortillas  Homemade Masa üëá 6 cups dried corn 3 quarts water 3 tbsp cal (calcium hydroxide) Bring the corn, water and cal to a boil and let cook for 30-60 minutes until the corn begins to soften. Then, turn off the heat and let the corn soak overnight. Wash the corn and rub corn kernels together with hands under running water. Grind the corn into masa with a molino and/or metate. You can also use a food processor, but this won‚Äôt give you as fine a masa. It does still work though. Shape masa into small balls and using a tortilla press, shape into tortillas. Place each ball between two pieces of thin plastic before pressing. Cook tortillas on hot pan or coral for 1-2 minutes per side. Place in a towel while you cook the tortillas, so that tortillas can further soften.

Decadence and joy without the tummy ache or sugar crash #homemade #muffins #homemaker FERMENTED RASPBERRY RECIPE Pre-Batter Ingredients: 1 cup sourdough discard 1 3/4 cup einkorn berries, milled into flour or about 3 cups whole wheat einkorn flour 1/2 cup sour cream 5 tbsp coconut sugar 1 cup milk  2 eggs 1 tsp vanilla 1/2 cup butter, melted (1 stick) Topping: 1 cup Walnuts (Optional) Combine all ingredients in a bowl. Batter should be pretty thick. Then, cover with plastic wrap and let sit to ferment overnight on the counter. Add walnuts to a bowl with warm water and a few pinches of salt. Let sit to sprout overnight. Final Batter Ingredients: 1/2 tsp salt  1 tsp baking soda 1 1/2 cups frozen raspberries In the morning, add salt, baking soda, and frozen raspberries to the batter. Use a cookie scoop or measuring cup to put the batter into a greased muffin pan. Strain the water and rinse the walnuts, then chop. Top muffins with the chopped walnuts. Bake at 425F for 5 minutes, then turn temp down to 375F and bake for 18 more minutes.
